WEBVTT

02:54.649 --> 02:56.052
Hey!

02:56.085 --> 02:58.120
Hey, man,
it's just me callin' you back.

02:59.722 --> 03:01.523
Hey,
I was just checkin' in,

03:01.556 --> 03:03.592
and seein' how your date
with what's-her-face went?

03:03.625 --> 03:07.163
- Oh, no, that's actually today.
- Oh!

03:07.196 --> 03:09.031
Yeah, all suited up
in a nonchalant way

03:09.065 --> 03:12.034
that signals my complete
and total sexual disinterest.

03:12.068 --> 03:13.970
Are you for real with that?

03:14.003 --> 03:15.805
Of course not.

03:15.838 --> 03:18.708
I actually think I'm on
the verge of a heart attack.

03:18.741 --> 03:21.476
Probably 'cause I haven't
gotten laid in, what, months?

03:21.509 --> 03:22.745
You mean, years?

03:22.778 --> 03:24.579
Shut up!

03:24.613 --> 03:27.850
But I mean, definitely
since my mom got really sick.

03:27.884 --> 03:30.518
Oh, no, no, this is an exciting
time for me, all right?

03:30.552 --> 03:32.755
I get to have some excitement

03:32.788 --> 03:34.957
- in my life.
- YOLO. Man, that's fine to say to me,

03:34.991 --> 03:37.093
but don't let the Boomers hear
you say shit like that, okay?

03:37.126 --> 03:40.897
You know what I mean.

03:40.930 --> 03:43.699
Man, you ever have it happen when
you feel like life is going one way,

03:43.733 --> 03:45.034
and then all of
a sudden, without blinking,

03:45.067 --> 03:48.436
just like everything changes?

03:48.470 --> 03:50.840
To a degree.

03:50.873 --> 03:53.809
I feel like
I'm losing my grip on reality,

03:53.843 --> 03:56.946
and might do
something terrible today.

03:56.979 --> 03:58.214
So that's why
you're packing the Magnums?

03:58.247 --> 04:00.216
Or I mean, the Micros?

04:00.249 --> 04:03.719
Yeah, Magnums for me, and I'll
be mailing you those Micros.

04:03.753 --> 04:08.024
Really, like,
I don't have to restrict myself

04:08.057 --> 04:10.927
to bare emotional
necessities anymore.

04:10.960 --> 04:13.029
Dude,
she needs your help, okay?

04:13.062 --> 04:14.230
You were doin'
what you had to do.

04:14.263 --> 04:15.731
Needed.

04:15.765 --> 04:16.966
Needed.

04:16.999 --> 04:18.466
Eason is watching over her now.

04:18.500 --> 04:20.168
I get it, but it doesn't mean

04:20.202 --> 04:22.470
that you can't still
call her and check in.

04:22.504 --> 04:23.806
Hey, who called who here?

04:24.907 --> 04:25.975
Sorry.

04:27.575 --> 04:29.845
You think this
has been easy for me?

04:29.879 --> 04:33.249
What do you wanna
talk about, Magnums again?

04:33.282 --> 04:35.117
Just a sec, my mother
needs help with the printer.

04:35.151 --> 04:37.153
Okay.

04:50.766 --> 04:52.667
Okay, I'm back.

04:52.702 --> 04:53.769
You still there?

04:55.271 --> 04:56.504
Max?

04:58.540 --> 04:59.909
What age?

04:59.942 --> 05:01.110
What?

05:02.878 --> 05:05.881
What age does life start
staring you in the face?

05:05.915 --> 05:08.184
You know, I'm,
I'm by a river right now,

05:08.217 --> 05:11.187
and there's this
bald eagle landing.

05:11.220 --> 05:12.922
You know, eagles mate for life.

05:12.955 --> 05:15.257
And I thought
you wanted talk about

05:15.291 --> 05:18.227
getting your rocks off,
and blowin' off some steam tonight?

05:18.260 --> 05:20.997
I'm serious, man.

05:21.030 --> 05:23.032
Oh, in their nest,
they also clench their fists,

05:23.065 --> 05:24.934
so they don't hurt their young.

05:24.967 --> 05:26.501
It doesn't always work out.

05:28.771 --> 05:31.606
Anyways, why don't you tell me
about this date, hmm?

05:31.639 --> 05:33.075
No red flags so far?

05:33.109 --> 05:35.845
Red...
No, no red flags.

05:35.878 --> 05:38.781
Actually, she seems amazing,
which is scary.

05:38.814 --> 05:41.717
Eager, which is, you know,
something that I get used to.

05:41.751 --> 05:45.021
Oh, oh, dude,
get this.

05:45.054 --> 05:47.056
Though, it has
not been addressed yet,

05:47.089 --> 05:48.758
- she... No, wait, wait.
- Oh, no!

05:48.791 --> 05:50.960
She is an English
and rhetoric major.

05:50.993 --> 05:52.128
Oh, dear God!

05:52.161 --> 05:53.863
But it's cool, though, dude.

05:53.896 --> 05:55.231
- No, no.
- Don't be academically prejudiced,

05:55.264 --> 05:56.832
- all right?
- Whatever!

05:56.866 --> 05:58.067
- It's your life, okay?
- Okay.

05:58.100 --> 05:59.634
But if you break her heart,

05:59.667 --> 06:01.837
just expect
countless tones, sighs,

06:01.871 --> 06:04.874
social media essays
about how you both shattered

06:04.907 --> 06:07.609
and nurtured
her personal growth.

06:07.642 --> 06:09.644
I am looking to keep
things light, thank you.

06:09.678 --> 06:10.746
Okay

06:10.780 --> 06:12.181
Well, bottom line is,

06:12.214 --> 06:13.883
come out swinging
with your guns loaded.

06:13.916 --> 06:15.851
You have
absolutely nothing to prove,

06:15.885 --> 06:19.121
so don't give some girl control
over your cortisol level.

06:19.155 --> 06:20.823
Jesus!

06:20.856 --> 06:23.259
All right, but
here's a serious question.

06:23.292 --> 06:26.729
What if I actually
start to fall for her?

06:27.830 --> 06:28.931
That's terrifying.

06:31.333 --> 06:32.902
Oh, shit!

06:32.935 --> 06:34.203
She just text me.
She's here.

06:34.236 --> 06:35.938
- What, like right now?
- Uh...

06:35.971 --> 06:37.273
- Yes, right now, actually.
- Okay.

06:37.306 --> 06:39.141
I'll ferry
you over the other side.

06:40.209 --> 06:41.677
Right.

06:41.710 --> 06:42.845
How nervous are you?

06:43.779 --> 06:46.148
Nervous?

06:46.182 --> 06:47.349
On a scale of 1 to 10,

06:47.383 --> 06:48.717
I could use Pep Talk 5.1.

06:50.052 --> 06:51.120
You're really
overthinking this.

06:51.153 --> 06:52.888
I know.
I know I am.

06:52.922 --> 06:54.757
- That's exactly why I need you.
- Fine.

06:54.790 --> 06:56.892
You're a tiger, okay?

06:56.926 --> 06:58.094
You're a lion!

06:58.127 --> 06:59.695
Roar!

06:59.728 --> 07:01.697
- I'm not gonna roar.
- You are Hercules,

07:01.730 --> 07:03.099
and your slashin' Minotaurs,

07:03.132 --> 07:04.700
like they're
dollar store discounts.

07:04.733 --> 07:06.135
Okay?

07:06.168 --> 07:07.736
- Okay.
- You're Hulk Hogan

07:07.770 --> 07:09.839
getting a settlement
for his sex tape.

07:09.872 --> 07:11.707
You got this shit, Max!

07:11.740 --> 07:13.242
Okay, I believe in you.

07:13.275 --> 07:14.677
Now, get out there,

07:14.710 --> 07:16.644
show her the jackpot she scored

07:16.679 --> 07:18.214
when she swiped right!

07:18.247 --> 07:19.949
Thank you.

07:19.982 --> 07:21.649
Tony Robbins doesn't
get me fired up like that.

07:21.684 --> 07:23.285
Who?

07:23.319 --> 07:24.887
Forget it.

07:24.920 --> 07:26.088
You're on your own from here.

07:26.122 --> 07:27.256
Bye.

07:34.163 --> 07:35.663
Hi.

07:35.698 --> 07:36.966
Hi.

07:38.434 --> 07:39.902
How are you?

07:39.935 --> 07:42.371
Well, I'm alive, so.

07:44.206 --> 07:45.741
The same, yep, same.

07:45.774 --> 07:46.809
Excellent.

07:48.477 --> 07:49.712
Like my car?

07:51.847 --> 07:56.852
It's a nice color, yeah.

07:56.886 --> 07:58.420
I'm just kidding.
My brother just dropped me off.

07:58.454 --> 08:01.290
Oh, Jesus.

08:01.323 --> 08:03.425
All right, all right,
this is how we're gonna kick things off?

08:03.459 --> 08:06.795
Had you goin'
for a second, didn't I?

08:06.829 --> 08:09.298
Can you imagine if
that's how I showed up?

08:09.331 --> 08:11.467
- I was gonna say...
- Red flag city.

08:11.500 --> 08:13.102
No, then again,
like I don't even have a car,

08:13.135 --> 08:15.137
so, like, who am I to speak?

08:15.171 --> 08:17.773
Taking care of your mom
the last year, was it?

08:17.806 --> 08:21.844
Yeah. Yeah, it didn't
leave me much time to make money.

08:21.877 --> 08:24.446
Not about to
hold that against you.

08:24.480 --> 08:27.049
Come on! We'll walk over to the theater.
It's not far.

08:27.082 --> 08:28.851
Cool, cool.

08:31.420 --> 08:33.889
Well,
you're not catfishing me,

08:33.923 --> 08:35.890
that's a good start.

08:35.924 --> 08:38.994
Likewise. You, um...

08:40.296 --> 08:42.198
You look amazing.

08:42.231 --> 08:43.265
Thank you.

08:45.768 --> 08:47.970
Whatever happens,
can we both agree that,

08:48.003 --> 08:49.271
as far as
the world is concerned,

08:49.305 --> 08:51.407
we did not meet on a dating app?

08:51.440 --> 08:53.976
Yeah, that's totally fine,

08:54.009 --> 08:57.346
but it's not like we met
on Mormon Mingle or anything.

08:57.379 --> 08:58.981
You're not wrong.

08:59.014 --> 09:00.482
That would, that would
definitely be weird.

09:00.516 --> 09:01.917
I agree.

09:01.951 --> 09:03.052
But, I mean, trust me,

09:03.085 --> 09:04.420
like, I totally get it.

09:04.453 --> 09:06.322
Like, I know
it can be a bit of like

09:06.355 --> 09:10.392
a Petri dish for wounded egos
and male awkwardness.

09:10.426 --> 09:12.428
But honestly,
if it wasn't for the internet,

09:12.461 --> 09:14.797
I don't know how
I'd meet anybody, so.

09:14.830 --> 09:17.032
I was talking to my brother
about that exact thing.

09:17.066 --> 09:18.834
- Oh, yeah?
- He said to me,

09:18.867 --> 09:20.869
"Avery, I don't know
if you're aware of this,

09:20.903 --> 09:23.239
but there are people
in this world, all around us,

09:23.272 --> 09:25.207
who venture to public places,

09:25.241 --> 09:27.142
go to people
they've never met before,

09:27.176 --> 09:29.278
and you become friends
with them right there,

09:29.311 --> 09:30.980
right on the spot."

09:31.013 --> 09:32.815
Well, no, that's like
science fiction to me.

09:32.848 --> 09:34.516
I don't know.

09:34.550 --> 09:36.318
I mean, I know
that's like what a normal,

09:36.352 --> 09:38.954
healthy, average person
is supposed to be doing,

09:38.988 --> 09:41.123
or so the world tells me.

09:41.156 --> 09:43.392
- And yet...
- Here we both are.

09:45.094 --> 09:46.962
Exactly, here we are.

09:48.230 --> 09:50.566
So if you think about it,

09:50.599 --> 09:54.003
I really should blame you
for enabling me.

09:54.036 --> 09:57.172
- Yeah, I was happy you could meet so soon.
- Yeah.

09:57.206 --> 09:59.108
I was lucky to
have the night off.

09:59.141 --> 10:01.977
When I'm looking to have fun,
I'm definitely an enabler,

10:02.011 --> 10:06.081
so look forward to the worst
decisions of your life.

10:06.115 --> 10:09.918
- Oh, okay! All right.
- I mean in a... good,

10:09.952 --> 10:11.587
wholesome,
girlfriend material kinda way.

10:11.620 --> 10:14.156
Who said
I was looking for a girlfriend?

10:14.189 --> 10:17.326
Um...

10:17.359 --> 10:20.029
- You know, I was...
- Oh, no, don't worry.

10:20.062 --> 10:22.164
No, no, no.
I'm sorry to spook you.

10:22.197 --> 10:24.033
- That was not graceful.
- No, no, no, no, are you kidding?

10:24.066 --> 10:25.834
No, I'm actually sorry.

10:25.868 --> 10:27.569
That whole...

10:27.603 --> 10:30.939
The whole foot in mouth thing is
kinda like my bread and butter,

10:30.973 --> 10:33.275
- and thank god you get it.
- Right?

10:33.309 --> 10:35.411
If you ever wanna exchange techniques,
you know, just please let me know.

10:35.444 --> 10:40.115
I kind of have a black belt in
conversational self-sabotage. Yeah.

10:40.149 --> 10:43.018
You're pretty honest.
I do like that.

10:43.052 --> 10:46.422
Not many guys would open a date
with confessions of self-sabotage.

10:48.324 --> 10:51.795
So this is a date then?

10:53.195 --> 10:55.564
I don't know.
Do you want it to be?

10:57.366 --> 11:01.370
I admit,
I'm not picketing the idea.

11:01.403 --> 11:04.139
I'm also cool with this not
labeling anything too quickly.

11:04.173 --> 11:06.475
You know, you can't
trust someone you just met.

11:06.508 --> 11:11.213
Never know who's out there,
or what their motivations are.

11:11.246 --> 11:13.415
I mean, we are going
to a movie tonight, right?

11:13.449 --> 11:15.117
- Yes, sir.
- Okay.

11:15.150 --> 11:18.287
And no, like,
BTK Dungeons, no underground,

11:18.320 --> 11:20.589
- and cell?
- Oh, no!

11:20.622 --> 11:23.092
BTK dungeons are after-movie destinations only.

11:23.125 --> 11:25.027
Right! Good.
I just wanted to make sure

11:25.060 --> 11:26.428
we weren't, like,
moving too fast, right?

11:26.462 --> 11:28.397
You know?

11:31.066 --> 11:33.602
But you were saying,

11:33.635 --> 11:36.605
you study, like,
English and rhetoric, right?

11:36.638 --> 11:38.440
- Yeah, I do.
- Okay.

11:38.474 --> 11:40.342
I'm in the throes of
regretting it, actually,

11:40.376 --> 11:42.211
- My dissertation...
- Really?

11:42.244 --> 11:45.347
...is melting,
like the width of the West.

11:45.381 --> 11:47.449
I found this
Le Guin's story called,

11:47.483 --> 11:48.650
"The Ones Who Walk
Away from Omelas"

11:48.685 --> 11:50.085
Oh, wow!

11:50.119 --> 11:51.653
You gotta meet my buddy, Dave.

11:51.688 --> 11:53.489
You two would get along
like fireworks.

11:56.024 --> 11:58.093
- I just...
- I didn't mean it.

11:58.127 --> 11:59.962
That's... Sorry.

11:59.995 --> 12:00.996
- Yes.
- Oh.

12:01.029 --> 12:02.064
- Yes.
- Okay.

12:02.097 --> 12:03.265
So...

12:03.298 --> 12:04.566
Um...

12:04.600 --> 12:06.402
- In Omelas...
- Mm-hmm.

12:06.435 --> 12:09.037
...every possible thing
that could ever make you happy

12:09.071 --> 12:12.174
is available on tap
every second of every day.

12:12.207 --> 12:15.644
No war, no crime, no poverty.

12:15.678 --> 12:18.715
- Well mandatory puppies, of course.
- Exactly.

12:18.748 --> 12:19.716
- Right.
- Paradise.

12:19.749 --> 12:21.417
Yeah.

12:21.450 --> 12:25.154
Except there's
this kid locked in a cage

12:25.187 --> 12:27.556
deep in a dungeon, tortured.

12:27.589 --> 12:29.191
Nobody talks about it.

12:29.224 --> 12:31.293
Everybody just accepts that

12:31.326 --> 12:33.395
the boy needs to
be tortured endlessly

12:33.429 --> 12:39.034
in order to maintain
the divinity of their paradise.

12:39.067 --> 12:43.405
Wow! A very positive
life-affirming story you got there.

12:43.439 --> 12:46.341
You could say that,
but you can't say that's more messed up

12:46.375 --> 12:47.710
than the world we live in now.

12:49.478 --> 12:51.246
I guess.

12:51.280 --> 12:54.349
So anyway, there are people
who refuse to take part

12:54.383 --> 12:55.584
in that whole system of living.

12:55.617 --> 12:57.186
- Right.
- And?

12:59.354 --> 13:03.659
Uh, they walk away
from the Omelas.

13:03.693 --> 13:06.028
Yeah. Yeah, exactly.

13:06.061 --> 13:07.996
So...

13:08.030 --> 13:10.265
You know, it's easy to side
with the people who walk away,

13:10.299 --> 13:14.269
but the two groups are
really doing the same thing.

13:14.303 --> 13:17.072
I mean, at the end, the kid is
still there being tortured, right?

13:19.541 --> 13:22.478
Okay, a totally
nonjudgmental question.

13:22.511 --> 13:24.079
Shoot.

13:24.112 --> 13:25.080
What would you do?

13:25.113 --> 13:26.448
What would I do?

13:26.482 --> 13:28.283
Yeah, if you had
that choice to make,

13:28.317 --> 13:31.119
what would, uh,
what would you choose?

13:31.153 --> 13:33.355
I think if I didn't
grapple with the answer,

13:33.388 --> 13:36.291
I wouldn't like
the story so much.

13:36.325 --> 13:38.695
Why? What about you?
What would you do?

13:44.233 --> 13:47.069
Well, I, I guess I just did it.

13:47.102 --> 13:48.570
What do you mean?

13:51.206 --> 13:53.475
Walked away.

13:53.509 --> 13:57.714
I mean, I just left
my mom on her death bed,

13:57.747 --> 14:01.116
'cause it got to be
too much for me.

14:01.149 --> 14:03.285
I read up on
Huntington's disease

14:03.318 --> 14:06.421
when you told me about it.
That's no easy thing.

14:08.090 --> 14:09.324
Yeah, I mean, it was...

14:11.326 --> 14:13.595
There were just
like only so many days

14:13.629 --> 14:16.365
I could watch her get sick.

14:16.398 --> 14:19.601
You know, it's like all
her memories together, fading,

14:19.635 --> 14:23.305
despite her still
being alive in front of me.

14:23.338 --> 14:25.340
I mean, like,
I was her lifeline.

14:25.374 --> 14:27.677
She honestly really
was like my best friend.

14:29.712 --> 14:32.381
I just got to like
a certain point where I just,

14:32.414 --> 14:36.285
I guess I just felt
like I gave, gave, and gave,

14:36.318 --> 14:38.855
until, like,
I felt as sick as she was.

14:38.888 --> 14:42.057
It's kinda like it was trading
in all her good memories for...

14:43.392 --> 14:44.560
something terrible.

14:48.163 --> 14:49.699
I mean, I still
don't know why, like,

14:49.732 --> 14:51.300
I chose to be her lifeline,

14:51.333 --> 14:55.304
or, like, why I chose to leave.

14:55.337 --> 14:58.340
Maybe there's just something
I haven't forgiven her for?

14:58.373 --> 15:00.309
I'm sorry.

15:00.342 --> 15:02.311
- I'm sorry, that was...
- That's okay.

15:02.344 --> 15:04.246
Yeah, I don't write, so.

15:04.279 --> 15:06.214
What would
your thesis say about that?

15:10.619 --> 15:14.489
Is it just me, or does this look
really uninviting all of a sudden?

15:14.523 --> 15:16.658
Yeah.
What is going on?

15:16.693 --> 15:18.160
I mean, I know
you kind of do have

15:18.193 --> 15:19.696
the school
shooter vibe going on.

15:19.729 --> 15:21.430
Maybe they heard
you were coming, and thought,

15:21.463 --> 15:23.465
- hey, you know, just in case.
- Oh, that's funny,

15:23.498 --> 15:26.168
- now that I know about the whole self-sabotage?
- Oh.

15:26.201 --> 15:28.637
I'm actually the manager here.

15:28.670 --> 15:30.272
Oh.

15:30.305 --> 15:31.808
- Nice.
- In fact,

15:31.841 --> 15:33.609
if you ever want free
tickets, I'm you're gal.

15:33.642 --> 15:34.811
Oh, no, that's too much.

15:34.844 --> 15:36.713
It's no trouble.

15:36.746 --> 15:39.716
God, it's like being on
a date with a Hollywood agent.

15:39.749 --> 15:41.483
Well, I don't know about that.

15:41.516 --> 15:43.185
I've got the white tickets,
not the green ones.

15:43.218 --> 15:44.754
Well, not yet.

15:44.787 --> 15:46.588
That's the spirit.

15:46.622 --> 15:48.590
Come on!

15:48.624 --> 15:50.793
Oh, be careful.

15:54.262 --> 15:55.765
Hey, you can't go any further!

15:55.798 --> 15:58.701
- Oh, I work here. What happened?
- Avery!

15:58.735 --> 16:01.303
Hey! What the hell?
What's going on in there?

16:01.336 --> 16:02.604
I was just
talking to Lucy about it.

16:02.638 --> 16:04.406
The phone rings, she picks up,

16:04.439 --> 16:06.208
there's a guy
on the phone saying,

16:06.241 --> 16:07.777
"There's a bomb under
the seat in Theater Three".

16:07.810 --> 16:09.411
We had to cancel
the whole "Evil Dead" screening.

16:09.444 --> 16:11.413
No postponement,
it's just not happening.

16:11.446 --> 16:12.949
That's crazy!
That's what we were gonna go see!

16:12.982 --> 16:14.650
- Yeah.
- Yeah, I was in the lobby

16:14.684 --> 16:15.818
when they cleared us out.
Look at my hands.

