to go in, you know?

35:22.765 --> 35:24.801
I mean, I would be
more than happy

35:24.834 --> 35:28.503
just taking a walk by the river,
getting to know you better.

35:29.972 --> 35:31.774
That's sweet, and I know.

35:33.642 --> 35:35.477
No one ever made memories
by playing it safe.

35:36.946 --> 35:38.613
There's an upstairs
room I wanna show you.

35:38.647 --> 35:42.584
All right,
I will bring the gun.

36:10.112 --> 36:13.515
This place is pretty
boarded and chained up, huh?

36:13.548 --> 36:15.751
It's to prevent
an infestation.

36:20.022 --> 36:23.558
All right,
talked a lot of shit earlier,

36:23.592 --> 36:25.627
I will go in first.

36:25.660 --> 36:27.797
You don't have to do that.

36:27.830 --> 36:30.398
Nothing to
be afraid of, right?

36:30.432 --> 36:31.901
Thank you.

37:09.872 --> 37:10.940
Max?

37:12.975 --> 37:14.676
Hello?

37:14.710 --> 37:16.478
Max, this isn't funny.

37:17.680 --> 37:18.881
Ha!

37:18.915 --> 37:20.515
Oh, my God!

37:20.548 --> 37:22.151
What the hell?

37:22.184 --> 37:23.853
That was awesome!

37:23.886 --> 37:25.187
Sorry.

37:25.221 --> 37:28.124
Don't do shit like that.

37:30.092 --> 37:31.894
Oh, sorry.

37:31.928 --> 37:34.830
Really old and creepy.

37:36.832 --> 37:39.802
So I'm doin' all right
for our first date?

37:39.835 --> 37:42.038
You could say that.

37:42.071 --> 37:45.708
It's been abandoned
for half a decade.

37:45.741 --> 37:48.744
For the town,
it's a place to be ignored.

37:48.778 --> 37:50.913
What's the story behind it?

37:50.947 --> 37:52.514
A ghost story?

37:52.547 --> 37:54.016
You wanna hear the ghost story?

37:54.050 --> 37:57.853
Well, I got my
white tickets, right?

37:57.887 --> 38:00.156
Okay, but shots first.

38:00.189 --> 38:02.624
Makes the story
more entertaining.

38:02.657 --> 38:04.659
Don't build
it up too much now.

38:13.069 --> 38:17.106
All right,
so they him Rotcreep.

38:17.139 --> 38:19.275
Rotcreep?

38:19.308 --> 38:20.608
Look,
Stephen King doesn't write

38:20.642 --> 38:21.944
small town urban legends.

38:21.978 --> 38:23.746
That's just what
he's called, okay?

38:23.779 --> 38:25.613
That's actually exactly
what Stephen King writes,

38:25.647 --> 38:28.184
but okay, please continue.

38:28.217 --> 38:32.855
Okay, so story goes...

38:32.888 --> 38:37.159
Once a year,
his hunger must be satisfied,

38:37.193 --> 38:41.731
one victim, or he'll act out
beyond these walls.

38:41.764 --> 38:44.300
You don't
actually believe this, right?

38:44.333 --> 38:46.802
Of course I do.

38:46.836 --> 38:48.838
I'll show you upstairs
where they say it all started.

38:48.871 --> 38:51.807
That's where Rotcreep
claimed his very first victims.

38:58.781 --> 38:59.949
What the hell was that?

38:59.982 --> 39:01.784
Hello?

39:01.817 --> 39:04.720
Raccoon, maybe?

39:04.754 --> 39:08.858
Yeah, so much
for preventing an infestation.

39:10.326 --> 39:12.161
Let's go up.

39:12.194 --> 39:13.763
You have the gun, don't you?

39:16.664 --> 39:18.234
All right.

39:18.267 --> 39:20.635
All right, Avery,
you officially got me

39:20.668 --> 39:23.139
out of my comfort zone.

39:23.172 --> 39:26.208
Well, it feels good to feel
something every once in a while.

39:55.071 --> 39:58.174
Not much different from
my room growing up, actually.

39:58.207 --> 40:00.076
Oh, yeah?

40:00.109 --> 40:03.746
Yeah, I mean, minus
all these wrestling posters.

40:03.779 --> 40:06.182
Who really up
and leaves all this stuff?

40:06.215 --> 40:08.851
You mean,
the fancy wrestling posters?

40:10.152 --> 40:11.687
True.

40:19.661 --> 40:21.297
Come look at these.

40:32.341 --> 40:35.111
Kids who lost their mom.

40:35.144 --> 40:37.179
Why are you showing me it?

40:37.213 --> 40:41.016
My buddy, Dave, would sure
approve of you guilt tripping me.

40:41.050 --> 40:44.153
Certainly not my motive.

40:44.186 --> 40:47.423
Sometimes there's more
reality than what's farfetched.

40:47.456 --> 40:48.891
Have a look.

41:02.371 --> 41:05.241
Rotcreep.

41:05.274 --> 41:07.042
Told you I didn't
make up the name.

41:10.312 --> 41:15.151
Looks like this kid's
got more demons than the house.

41:15.184 --> 41:16.785
The house is just a vessel.

41:18.787 --> 41:20.322
What do you mean?

41:20.356 --> 41:23.359
Apparently,
Rotcreep is bound to the house,

41:23.392 --> 41:24.426
as long as it's fed.

41:26.962 --> 41:30.733
Right, right,
once a year, you mentioned.

41:30.766 --> 41:32.935
Now you're qualified
to give the ghost tour.

41:35.004 --> 41:38.040
Yeah, next,
you're gonna tell me,

41:38.073 --> 41:41.177
well, we both know exactly
what you're going to say,

41:41.210 --> 41:44.480
tonight, he is needing
to feed , right?

41:44.513 --> 41:46.749
All good ghost stories
escalate quickly?

41:49.952 --> 41:51.320
Come sit on the bed with me.

41:54.423 --> 41:57.493
Okay, um, look.

41:57.526 --> 42:01.463
You know, I know I said,
I don't believe in ghosts,

42:01.497 --> 42:05.201
but I'm starting to think whether I believe
doesn't matter all that much to the ghost.

42:05.234 --> 42:08.304
Just sit for one moment,
then we'll go. I promise.

42:20.382 --> 42:22.418
- I'm good.
- You sure?

42:22.451 --> 42:27.022
Yeah, I'm just...
having second thoughts.

42:27.056 --> 42:29.391
I know, there's just
something that I wanna say.

42:34.029 --> 42:36.465
Um...

42:36.498 --> 42:38.901
I think I'm really
starting to like you.

42:38.934 --> 42:40.436
You're a good guy, Max.

42:40.469 --> 42:41.837
You're a good guy.

42:44.206 --> 42:46.342
Thank you for saying so.

42:46.375 --> 42:48.811
I haven't really
heard that in a while,

42:48.844 --> 42:50.879
as you could imagine.

42:54.283 --> 42:55.784
Are you...

42:55.818 --> 42:58.854
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

42:58.887 --> 43:00.456
There's just something
that I haven't told you,

43:00.489 --> 43:02.224
and it's a lot worse

43:02.258 --> 43:04.126
than not being the manager
of that movie theater.

43:06.262 --> 43:08.230
Uh...

43:08.264 --> 43:11.033
You remember my paper on "The
Ones Who Walk Away from Omelas"?

43:12.368 --> 43:14.370
Yeah, yeah.

43:14.403 --> 43:16.538
Well, a number of years ago,

43:16.572 --> 43:19.174
I had a similar
decision to make,

43:19.208 --> 43:21.510
my family versus a stranger.

43:23.245 --> 43:25.447
Okay.

43:25.481 --> 43:29.418
I think that my paper has always
been a way of justifying my guilt.

43:29.451 --> 43:33.889
I guess you could say,
I decided not to walk away.

43:37.226 --> 43:39.261
Okay.

43:39.295 --> 43:42.064
You're really
starting to weird me out.

43:42.097 --> 43:44.033
But you understand,

43:44.066 --> 43:46.468
because of what you went through
with your mom, don't you?

43:46.502 --> 43:49.071
Because of your past?

43:49.104 --> 43:52.441
Whatever happens, don't
think that this is easy for me.

43:52.474 --> 43:57.212
See, Max, this
isn't just any home.

43:57.246 --> 43:59.048
This is my childhood home.

44:10.025 --> 44:11.427
I thought you said
he'd go down!

44:11.460 --> 44:13.028
- Sorry, Max.
- I thought he would.

44:13.062 --> 44:14.630
Whoa, don't!
You get out of my way!

44:14.663 --> 44:17.099
Out of my way!
I'm leaving right now!

44:17.132 --> 44:19.201
- That's not gonna happen, Max.
- We told you all this to prepare you, Max.

44:19.234 --> 44:21.270
You asked about the scariest
thing that's ever happened to me.

44:21.303 --> 44:22.971
I'm afraid it's still happening.

44:23.005 --> 44:24.406
We ran from this place
as soon as we could,

44:24.440 --> 44:26.275
as far as we could,
as fast as we could,

44:26.308 --> 44:28.010
but it didn't matter.

44:28.043 --> 44:31.113
Rotcreep always came for us,
until we realized

44:31.146 --> 44:34.016
that someone could take Phillip's
place here in this house,

44:34.049 --> 44:37.319
and be his new... interest.

44:37.353 --> 44:40.923
I use the word stalker earlier to
put it in terms you'd understand.

44:40.956 --> 44:43.492
He died, but that didn't stop
him from coming after Philip.

44:43.525 --> 44:45.294
The same habits
in life as in death.

44:45.327 --> 44:46.929
We dropped a kid
here just last week,

44:46.962 --> 44:48.330
and thought
Phillip would be safe again,

44:48.364 --> 44:51.033
but it seems
Rotcreep it still hungry.

44:51.066 --> 44:52.334
And when he doesn't
get what he wants,

44:52.368 --> 44:55.104
he comes for me, wherever I am.

44:58.474 --> 45:00.175
Happened this morning.

45:00.209 --> 45:02.244
I barely got away.

45:02.277 --> 45:08.150
Just one touch
rots you from the outside in.

45:08.183 --> 45:11.053
For what it's worth,
it's not personal, man.

45:11.086 --> 45:13.655
We're just trying to stay alive.

45:13.690 --> 45:15.224
Stop, stop!

45:15.257 --> 45:17.694
Stop, stop!

45:17.727 --> 45:19.194
You step out of
the way right now,

45:19.228 --> 45:20.429
and I'm...

45:31.407 --> 45:34.543
Blanks, so you'd feel safe.

45:34.576 --> 45:37.312
In case her nice tits
weren't enough.

45:37.346 --> 45:40.048
- Avery?
- I'm sorry, Max.

45:40.082 --> 45:41.350
Sorry, Max.

45:54.396 --> 45:56.365
See,
I told you he'd go down.

46:00.636 --> 46:02.304
I'll get his legs.

46:13.615 --> 46:15.184
Zip ties.

46:27.396 --> 46:28.997
Pull him closer.

46:50.753 --> 46:52.087
Don't get too turned on now.

46:52.120 --> 46:54.189
Shut up, Phillip!

47:03.232 --> 47:06.568
Broke ass mother fucker!

47:07.669 --> 47:09.271
It's not working!

47:28.357 --> 47:29.826
Really?

47:31.293 --> 47:34.062
- Sorry, Max.
- Avery, come on!

47:44.406 --> 47:47.209
When you wake up, drink this.

47:47.242 --> 47:50.379
It'll make things easier,
trust me.

47:50.412 --> 47:52.614
I assure you, it'll be a hell
of a lot shorter than Phillip's,

47:52.648 --> 47:55.183
and maybe mine.

47:55.217 --> 47:57.820
You're about to
understand it all.

49:03.886 --> 49:06.355
Help!

50:05.682 --> 50:06.683
Hey, just stay back!

50:16.859 --> 50:18.695
I'm not gonna hurt you.

50:20.529 --> 50:22.564
All right?

50:22.597 --> 50:24.199
You just come out.

50:25.400 --> 50:26.501
You come out.

50:27.636 --> 50:28.805
That's right.

50:34.643 --> 50:37.612
Whoa, whoa, hey, hey, hey.

50:37.646 --> 50:39.514
Whoa.

50:39.548 --> 50:41.349
Hi.

50:41.383 --> 50:42.685
Hi.

50:42.719 --> 50:44.519
I'm not gonna
hurt you, that's...

50:44.553 --> 50:45.855
My name's Max.

51:04.741 --> 51:06.008
This is yours?

51:10.579 --> 51:12.949
Okay, okay, who are you, kid?

51:12.982 --> 51:14.316
Who are you?

51:14.349 --> 51:15.985
Like I said, my name is Max.

51:17.552 --> 51:19.287
How long
you been hiding in there?

51:20.790 --> 51:22.925
I don't know.

51:22.959 --> 51:25.895
All right, well,
how did you get here?

51:25.928 --> 51:27.562
That girl.

51:30.967 --> 51:33.568
Avery, she brought you here?

51:38.573 --> 51:39.809
All right, listen.

51:41.409 --> 51:42.879
I already tried that!

51:46.515 --> 51:47.984
No, no, no, don't open it!

51:48.017 --> 51:49.819
He'll get you!

51:49.852 --> 51:51.486
It?

51:51.520 --> 51:53.856
Rotcreep.

51:56.058 --> 51:59.028
- I'm just gonna make sure the coast is clear, okay?
- No, no, no, no.

52:11.540 --> 52:14.010
The hallway's empty.

52:14.043 --> 52:15.711
It's okay.

52:17.680 --> 52:19.882
What the hell was that?

52:21.684 --> 52:23.753
You think I didn't
try to open the door already?

52:23.786 --> 52:27.690
I told you.
You didn't listen!

52:27.723 --> 52:30.760
It doesn't care
if you believe in it or not.

52:45.775 --> 52:48.610
Do you have anything to drink?

52:48.643 --> 52:50.545
Only this.

52:52.682 --> 52:54.616
That's for adults!

52:56.052 --> 52:58.120
Ew!

52:59.521 --> 53:01.891
What is that, gasoline?

53:05.027 --> 53:06.661
You weren't
supposed to drink that.

53:08.764 --> 53:12.534
Taste like... burning.

53:14.203 --> 53:17.173
Okay, how the hell
do I get outta here?

53:17.206 --> 53:19.141
We don't!

53:27.649 --> 53:28.684
Hey!

53:30.119 --> 53:32.121
Hey, I'm sorry. Okay?

53:32.154 --> 53:34.690
Clearly, you weren't
supposed to be here,

53:34.724 --> 53:36.424
but you still are.
All right?

53:36.458 --> 53:37.425
You're doing something right.

53:37.459 --> 53:38.526
I'm sorry.

53:40.662 --> 53:42.031
All right?

53:45.735 --> 53:49.571
My dad has to pour drinks...

53:50.907 --> 53:52.875
Okay.

53:52.909 --> 53:54.110
Okay.

53:54.143 --> 53:56.145
So what do we do?

53:56.178 --> 53:58.881
Out there,
it's all boarded up.

53:58.915 --> 54:01.083
Every window, every door!

54:01.117 --> 54:05.654
There's not enough room
for both of us to hide.

54:05.688 --> 54:08.024
You've been hiding in there
this whole time?

54:08.057 --> 54:10.159
I tried to go in the kitchen,

54:10.192 --> 54:14.596
but that was a bad idea
going down there.

54:14.629 --> 54:16.699
- What happened?
- You don't wanna find out.

54:16.732 --> 54:19.835
But whatever happens,
stay away from his bedroom!

54:19.869 --> 54:21.704
Never go into his room.

54:28.778 --> 54:33.115
Okay.

54:33.149 --> 54:36.584
Okay, well, I'm glad
that you're able to get away.

54:36.618 --> 54:40.856
Even my house cat plays
with mice before it kills them.

54:40.890 --> 54:42.657
Remember, you're here now.

54:44.260 --> 54:46.494
Yeah.

54:46.528 --> 54:47.897
Yeah.

54:47.930 --> 54:49.732
Okay.

54:49.765 --> 54:52.168
Hey, you never
told me your name.

54:52.201 --> 54:53.703
It's Rudy.

54:53.736 --> 54:55.938
- Rudy, son of Sam Quincy.
- Mm-hmm.

54:55.972 --> 54:57.239
I lost my bike.

54:57.273 --> 54:59.041
Avery said
she knew where it was.

55:00.776 --> 55:02.778
She...

55:02.812 --> 55:04.612
And now, I'm here.

55:04.646 --> 55:05.848
Okay.

55:05.881 --> 55:07.683
All right, Rudy.

55:07.717 --> 55:10.518
Okay, let's get you back
up on your feet, all right?

55:10.552 --> 55:12.254
And let's try to
get out of this together.

55:12.288 --> 55:14.924
You think we can do this?

55:14.957 --> 55:16.258
Put out your hand.

55:18.060 --> 55:21.130
Little fingers can't break open
windows and doors.

55:21.163 --> 55:24.066
These,
however, along with these,

55:24.100 --> 55:25.301
we got a chance!

55:25.334 --> 55:26.836
Faith?

55:26.869 --> 55:29.138
What?

55:29.171 --> 55:32.507
My mom said when you're down
you have to have faith.

55:34.910 --> 55:37.179
All right.

55:37.213 --> 55:40.082
All right, I guess
it's not such bad advice.

55:40.116 --> 55:41.784
So you're with me?

55:41.817 --> 55:43.585
Yeah?

55:43.618 --> 55:44.652
All right.

55:44.687 --> 55:45.653
Hey, that doesn't work.

55:45.688 --> 55:47.555
Hey!

55:47.589 --> 55:48.691
Hey, trust me.

55:48.724 --> 55:51.559
- Okay?
- Okay.

55:51.593 --> 55:53.829
Okay, Rudy.

55:53.863 --> 55:55.164
All right, when I open it,

55:55.197 --> 55:57.299
no hesitations, okay?

55:57.333 --> 56:00.202
We're walking straight out
and down the stairs.

56:00.236 --> 56:02.238
- You got it?
- Got it.

56:02.271 --> 56:04.774
I guess we're supposed to be tied
up and not running around together?

56:04.807 --> 56:06.142
That's right.

56:09.677 --> 56:10.746
The hallway's empty.

56:10.780 --> 56:12.081
Okay.

56:12.114 --> 56:13.648
On three.

56:13.682 --> 56:16.719
One, two...

56:16.752 --> 56:17.987
Okay.

56:18.020 --> 56:19.288
Go, go, go, go!

56:26.128 --> 56:28.130
Help me with this one!

56:29.298 --> 56:30.598
That's on too tight.

56:30.632 --> 56:32.334
It's way too tight.

56:32.368 --> 56:34.236
Now, you cover
your ears, all right?

56:40.976 --> 56:42.610
Wow!

56:42.644 --> 56:44.046
Just a few more,
and then we push it.

56:44.080 --> 56:45.381
Come on!
Squeeze through, Rudy!

56:49.251 --> 56:50.886
- Come on!
- More!

56:50.920 --> 56:52.088
Not goin' in!

56:52.121 --> 56:53.222
Squeeze through!

56:53.255 --> 56:54.256
- Come on, push!
- You!

56:54.290 --> 56:55.324
Push!

56:55.357 --> 56:56.692
Come on!

56:58.127 --> 56:59.195
I'm coming!

57:01.330 --> 57:02.932
Run! Run!

57:02.965 --> 57:04.066
The hell?

57:04.100 --> 57:05.734
Rudy? What are you doing?

57:05.768 --> 57:07.803
Oh, my!
Phillip, get him!

57:07.837 --> 57:09.371
Max, you should not have
let the boy take your place.

57:09.405 --> 57:11.373
Avery, Avery,
you let me

57:11.407 --> 57:13.675
- outta here right now.
- There's still no way out of this!

57:13.709 --> 57:15.277
- Please, Avery, please.
- I'm sorry. I wish it were that easy!

57:15.311 --> 57:16.812
- I'm begging you! I'm begging you, please!
- I can't, Max!

57:23.352 --> 57:25.221
I'm not gonna act
like I didn't deserve that.

57:27.223 --> 57:29.692
I'm gonna make sure
to get Rudy back for you.

59:39.822 --> 59:40.789
Wait, wait!

59:40.823 --> 59:42.157
Wait, wait!

59:42.191 --> 59:44.326
No, no, no, no!

59:44.360 --> 59:45.794
No, no!

59:45.828 --> 59:46.962
No!

01:02:01.063 --> 01:02:04.066
<i>Go on. Why don't you
tell Daddy what you're doing?</i>

01:02:04.099 --> 01:02:05.467
<i>It's just Oscar, Daddy.</i>

01:02:05.501 --> 01:02:07.236
<i>I'm teaching him how to swim.</i>

01:02:07.269 --> 01:02:09.204
<i>I'm not sure
if robots know how to swim,</i>

01:02:09.238 --> 01:02:11.306
<i>but I just wanted
to win the race.</i>

01:02:11.340 --> 01:02:13.275
<i>That's cute.</i>

01:02:13.308 --> 01:02:15.043
<i>Are you gonna win your swim
meet tomorrow, Phillip?</i>

01:02:15.077 --> 01:02:17.513
<i>How 'bout you come
teach Daddy how to swim?</i>

01:02:17.546 --> 01:02:20.115
<i>I'll make a change
to my swimsuit, Phillip.</i>

01:02:20.149 --> 01:02:23.252
<i>Daddy, Phillip,
are you two down there?</i>

01:02:28.590 --> 01:02:29.958
<i>Creep.</i>

01:03:45.200 --> 01:03:46.535
Go on!

01:03:48.337 --> 01:03:50.038
Remember, Max...

01:03:50.072 --> 01:03:51.273
...Rotcreep only needs
one of you!

01:03:56.411 --> 01:03:59.248
I'm sorry, Max!

01:03:59.281 --> 01:04:00.783
I'm sorry!

01:04:00.817 --> 01:04:03.285
I really tried to
get away and get help.

01:04:23.472 --> 01:04:26.141
I know, buddy.

01:04:26.174 --> 01:04:27.242
I know.

01:04:28.811 --> 01:04:30.546
I really tried.

01:04:30.579 --> 01:04:33.515
I know, but you remember
what I told you earlier?

01:04:33.549 --> 01:04:37.352
The same goes
for your legs, all right?

01:04:37.386 --> 01:04:40.155
How are you supposed to
